      </div>

      <!-- Interpretation -->
      <div class="space-y-2.5">
        <div class="border-l-2 border-orange-300 pl-4">
          <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-700 mb-0.5">
            Macro–micro gap reveals where fragility concentrates
          </p>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-500">
            The S&P 500 macro RG ({fmt(macroSP.rg10)}) sits {fmt(macroSP.rg10 - buUSMed)} points above the
            equal-weighted company median ({fmt(buUSMed)}). The difference reflects market-cap weighting:
            Tesla, Broadcom, AMD — the permanent super-narrative fixtures — are also among the largest
            index constituents. A passive index investor's effective RG exposure is substantially higher
            than the median company in the index implies.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="border-l-2 border-red-300 pl-4">
          <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-700 mb-0.5">
            Approaching the 1999 peak — with a different composition
          </p>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-500">
            At {fmt(macroSP.rg10)}, the S&P 500 macro RG stands at {(macroSP.rg10 / spLRMax * 100).toFixed(0)}%
            of its December 1999 peak of {fmt(spLRMax)}, and {(macroSP.rg10 / spLRAvg).toFixed(1)}× the
