            technology. Today the extreme valuations are even more concentrated: the same four companies
            recur in the top decile across all measured periods.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="border-l-2 border-teal-300 pl-4">
          <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-700 mb-0.5">
            Geographic hierarchy holds at both levels
          </p>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-500">
            Macro: S&P 500 {fmt(macroSP.rg10)} vs DAX 40 {fmt(macroDAX.rg10)} — ratio {(macroSP.rg10 / macroDAX.rg10).toFixed(1)}×.
            Bottom-up: US median {fmt(buUSMed)} vs DE median {fmt(buDEMed)} — ratio {(buUSMed / buDEMed).toFixed(1)}×.
            The different methodologies produce different absolute levels but the same structural ordering.
            US equities carry meaningfully higher valuation multiples at every level of analysis.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ── 5i. Sector vs. Country ──────────────────────────────────────────── -->
    <section class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-1">Sector vs. Country: What Drives the Reality Gap?</h2>
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 mb-1">
        With {scN} companies across {SC_COUNTRIES.length} markets, we can decompose RG variation into a
        <em>sector effect</em> (same sector, different countries) and a <em>country effect</em> (same country,
        different sectors). Which signal is stronger?
      </p>
      <p class="text-xs text-gray-400 mb-6">Snapshot: most-recent available RG10 per company. One company per row in the decomposition.</p>

      <!-- R² comparison cards -->
      <div class="grid grid-cols-2 gap-4 mb-8" style="max-width:420px">
        <div class="border border-gray-200 rounded-md p-4 text-center">
          <div class="text-3xl font-light text-orange-500 mb-1">{scSectorR2}%</div>
          <div class="text-xs font-semibold text-gray-600">Variance explained</div>
          <div class="text-xs text-gray-400 mt-0.5">by Sector alone</div>
        </div>
        <div class="border border-gray-200 rounded-md p-4 text-center">
          <div class="text-3xl font-light text-blue-500 mb-1">{scCountryR2}%</div>
          <div class="text-xs font-semibold text-gray-600">Variance explained</div>
          <div class="text-xs text-gray-400 mt-0.5">by Country alone</div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <p class="text-xs text-gray-400 mb-8">R² measures how much of the cross-company RG variance is captured by knowing only the sector or only the country. Neither model uses both simultaneously.</p>

      <!-- Sector ranking bar chart -->
      <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-700 mb-3">Sector Median RG10 (all markets combined, n ≥ 3)</h3>
      <div class="space-y-1.5 mb-8">
        {scSectorRows.map(row => (
          <div class="flex items-center gap-2 text-xs">
            <span class="text-gray-500 shrink-0" style="width:170px; text-align:right;">{row.sector}</span>
            <div class="flex-1 bg-gray-100 rounded-sm h-5 relative" style="max-width:260px">
              <div class="h-5 rounded-sm" style={`width:${(row.med/scMaxSectorMed*100).toFixed(1)}%;background:${scCellBg(row.med)}`}></div>
            </div>
            <span class="font-mono font-semibold text-gray-700 w-8 shrink-0">{row.med.toFixed(2)}</span>
            <span class="text-gray-400 shrink-0">n={row.n}</span>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>

      <!-- Cross-tabulation: sector × country -->
      <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-700 mb-2">Cross-Tab: Median RG10 by Sector × Country</h3>
      <p class="text-xs text-gray-400 mb-3">Cells with a single company show that company's value. Empty = no data. Heat: teal = low, orange = medium, red = high.</p>
      <div class="overflow-x-auto mb-6">
        <table class="text-xs border-collapse w-full" style="min-width:480px">
          <thead>
            <tr class="text-gray-500">
              <th class="text-left px-2 py-1.5 font-medium border-b border-gray-200" style="min-width:130px">Sector</th>
              {SC_COUNTRIES.map(c => <th class="text-center px-2 py-1.5 font-semibold border-b border-gray-200">{c}</th>)}
              <th class="text-right px-2 py-1.5 font-medium border-b border-gray-200">All</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            {scSectorRows.map(row => (
              <tr class="border-b border-gray-50 hover:bg-gray-50/50">
                <td class="px-2 py-1.5 text-gray-700 font-medium">{row.sector}</td>
                {SC_COUNTRIES.map(c => {
                  const v = scCross[row.sector]?.[c] ?? null;
                  return (
                    <td class="px-2 py-1.5 text-center font-mono"
                      style={`background:${scCellBg(v)}`}>
                      {v !== null ? v.toFixed(2) : <span class="text-gray-300">—</span>}
                    </td>
                  );
                })}
                <td class="px-2 py-1.5 text-right font-mono font-semibold text-gray-700">{row.med.toFixed(2)}</td>
              </tr>
            ))}
            <!-- Country median row -->
            <tr class="border-t-2 border-gray-300 bg-gray-50">
              <td class="px-2 py-1.5 text-gray-600 font-semibold">Country median</td>
              {SC_COUNTRIES.map(c => {
                const v = scCountryVals[c] ? median([...scCountryVals[c]].sort((a,b)=>a-b)) : null;
                return (
                  <td class="px-2 py-1.5 text-center font-mono font-semibold text-gray-700"
                    style={`background:${scCellBg(v)}`}>
                    {v !== null ? v.toFixed(2) : '—'}
                  </td>
                );
              })}
              <td class="px-2 py-1.5 text-right font-mono font-semibold text-gray-900">{scMean.toFixed(2)}</td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>

      <!-- Interpretation -->
      <div class="space-y-2.5">
        <div class="border-l-2 border-orange-300 pl-4">
          <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-700 mb-0.5">
            Sector explains {scSectorR2 > scCountryR2 ? 'more' : 'less'} variance than country ({scSectorR2}% vs {scCountryR2}%)
          </p>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-500">
            Knowing only a company's sector accounts for {scSectorR2}% of the cross-company variation in RG10.
            Knowing only its country accounts for {scCountryR2}%. Both effects are real, but
            {scSectorR2 > scCountryR2 ? 'sector membership is the stronger signal' : 'country provides the stronger signal'}.
            This explains why France and Switzerland rank above Germany in the geographic analysis —
            their indices are dominated by luxury goods and pharmaceuticals, two sectors with structurally elevated narrative premiums.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="border-l-2 border-gray-300 pl-4">
          <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-700 mb-0.5">High-RG sectors are consistently high across borders</p>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-500">
            {scSectorRows.slice(0,2).map(r=>r.sector).join(' and ')} sit at the top of the sector ranking
            regardless of the country of incorporation. Conversely, {scSectorRows.slice(-2).map(r=>r.sector).join(' and ')} cluster
            at the bottom in every market. The sector ceiling and floor are more stable than the country ceiling and floor.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="border-l-2 border-gray-300 pl-4">
          <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-700 mb-0.5">Country adds a systematic level shift above the sector baseline</p>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-500">
            US companies in the same sector as their European or Japanese peers consistently command a higher RG.
            This residual country premium — visible in the cross-tab — represents the structural US narrative premium
            that cannot be explained by sector composition alone.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ── 6. RG vs Simpler Metrics ─────────────────────────────────────── -->
    <section class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-1">{tc.metricComparison.heading}</h2>
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 mb-2">{tc.metricComparison.subheading}</p>
      <p class="text-xs text-gray-400 mb-6">{tc.metricComparison.sampleNote}</p>

      <!-- Main comparison table with inline bars -->
      <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-700 mb-3">{tc.metricComparison.comparisonTableHeading}</h3>
      <div class="border border-gray-200 rounded-md overflow-hidden mb-8 text-xs">
        <table class="w-full border-collapse">
          <thead>
            <tr class="bg-gray-50 text-gray-500 uppercase tracking-wide">
              <th class="text-left px-3 py-2 font-medium">{tc.metricComparison.colMetric}</th>
              <th class="text-right px-3 py-2 font-medium">{tc.metricComparison.colN}</th>
              <th class="text-right px-3 py-2 font-medium">{tc.metricComparison.colLowAvg}</th>
              <th class="text-right px-3 py-2 font-medium">{tc.metricComparison.colHighAvg}</th>
              <th class="px-3 py-2 font-medium" style="width:120px;">Visual</th>
              <th class="text-right px-3 py-2 font-medium font-semibold text-gray-700">{tc.metricComparison.colSpread}</th>
              <th class="text-right px-3 py-2 font-medium">{tc.metricComparison.colRho}</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            {retroMetrics.map(m => (
              <tr class="border-t border-gray-100">
                <td class="px-3 py-2 text-gray-700 font-medium" style="max-width: 200px;">
                  <span class="block text-xs font-semibold text-gray-800">{m.key.toUpperCase()}</span>
                </td>
                <td class="px-3 py-2 text-right font-mono text-gray-500">{m.n}</td>
                <td class={`px-3 py-2 text-right font-mono font-semibold ${m.inverted ? 'text-gray-600' : 'text-teal-700'}`}>
                  {m.inverted ? '' : '+'}{fmt(m.lowAvg, 0)}%
                </td>
                <td class={`px-3 py-2 text-right font-mono ${m.inverted ? 'text-teal-700 font-semibold' : 'text-gray-600'}`}>
                  {m.inverted ? '+' : ''}{fmt(m.highAvg, 0)}%
                </td>
                <td class="px-3 py-2">
                  <div class="flex items-center gap-1" style="height:14px;">
                    <div class="bg-teal-400/60 rounded-sm" style={`height:10px; width:${Math.round((m.inverted ? m.highAvg : m.lowAvg) / maxAvgRet * 60)}px;`} />
                    <div class="bg-gray-300/80 rounded-sm" style={`height:10px; width:${Math.round((m.inverted ? m.lowAvg : m.highAvg) / maxAvgRet * 60)}px;`} />
                  </div>
                </td>
                <td class={`px-3 py-2 text-right font-mono font-semibold ${Math.abs(m.spread) >= 30 ? 'text-gray-900' : 'text-gray-500'}`}>
                  {m.spread >= 0 ? '+' : ''}{fmt(m.spread, 0)}%
                </td>
                <td class="px-3 py-2 text-right font-mono text-gray-600">
                  {m.rho != null ? (m.rho >= 0 ? '+' : '') + m.rho.toFixed(2) : '—'}
                </td>
              </tr>
            ))}
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>

      <!-- Quartile breakdown for RG10 and P/G side by side -->
      <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-700 mb-3">{tc.metricComparison.quartileHeading}</h3>
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 gap-6 mb-8" style="grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(280px, 1fr));">
        {retroMetrics.slice(0, 3).map(m => (
          <div class="border border-gray-200 rounded-md overflow-hidden text-xs">
            <div class="bg-gray-50 px-3 py-2 font-semibold text-gray-700 border-b border-gray-200">
              {m.key.toUpperCase()} — {tc.metricComparison.quartileHeading}
            </div>
            <div class="p-3 space-y-2">
              {[m.q1, m.q2, m.q3, m.q4].map((q, i) => (
                <div class="flex items-center gap-2">
                  <span class="text-gray-400 w-4 shrink-0">Q{i+1}</span>
                  <div class="flex-1 bg-gray-100 rounded-sm h-5 relative">
                    <div
                      class={`h-5 rounded-sm ${q.avgRet >= 70 ? 'bg-teal-400/70' : q.avgRet >= 40 ? 'bg-accent/60' : 'bg-gray-300'}`}
                      style={`width: ${maxAvgRet > 0 ? Math.round(Math.max(0, q.avgRet) / maxAvgRet * 100) : 0}%`}
                    />
                  </div>
                  <span class={`font-mono w-14 text-right shrink-0 ${q.avgRet >= 70 ? 'text-teal-700 font-semibold' : 'text-gray-600'}`}>
                    {q.avgRet >= 0 ? '+' : ''}{fmt(q.avgRet, 0)}%
                  </span>
                  <span class="text-gray-400 w-5 shrink-0 text-center">n={q.n}</span>
                </div>
              ))}
            </div>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>

      <!-- Verdict box -->
      <div class="border border-gray-200 rounded-md bg-gray-50/50 px-5 py-4 mb-8">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-700 mb-1">{tc.metricComparison.verdictHeading}</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">{tc.metricComparison.verdictBody}</p>
      </div>

      <!-- Illustrative cases -->
      <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-700 mb-2">{tc.metricComparison.casesHeading}</h3>
      <p class="text-xs text-gray-400 mb-3">{tc.metricComparison.casesNote}</p>
      <div class="border border-gray-200 rounded-md overflow-hidden text-xs">
        <table class="w-full border-collapse">
          <thead>
            <tr class="bg-gray-50 text-gray-500 uppercase tracking-wide">
              <th class="text-left px-3 py-2 font-medium">{tc.metricComparison.colCompany}</th>
              <th class="text-right px-3 py-2 font-medium">{tc.metricComparison.colRG10}</th>
              <th class="text-right px-3 py-2 font-medium">{tc.metricComparison.colPG}</th>
              <th class="text-right px-3 py-2 font-medium">{tc.metricComparison.colMTE}</th>
              <th class="text-right px-3 py-2 font-medium font-semibold text-gray-700">{tc.metricComparison.colReturn}</th>
              <th class="text-left px-3 py-2 font-medium">{tc.metricComparison.colCase}</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            {illustrativeCases.map(c => {
              const caseColor = c.caseType === 'consistent'
                ? 'text-teal-600'
                : c.caseType === 'exception'
                ? 'text-orange-600'
                : 'text-gray-400';
              return (
                <tr class="border-t border-gray-100">
                  <td class="px-3 py-2 font-medium text-gray-700">{c.company}</td>
                  <td class="px-3 py-2 text-right font-mono text-gray-600">{c.rg10.toFixed(2)}</td>
                  <td class="px-3 py-2 text-right font-mono text-gray-600">{c.pg != null ? c.pg.toFixed(2) : '—'}</td>
                  <td class="px-3 py-2 text-right font-mono text-gray-600">{c.mte != null ? c.mte.toFixed(1) : '—'}</td>
                  <td class={`px-3 py-2 text-right font-mono font-semibold ${c.ret > 0 ? 'text-gray-800' : 'text-gray-500'}`}>
                    {c.ret > 0 ? '+' : ''}{c.ret}%
                  </td>
                  <td class={`px-3 py-2 text-xs ${caseColor}`}>
                    {(tc.metricComparison.caseTypes as any)[c.caseType]}
                  </td>
                </tr>
              );
            })}
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ── 7. What RG might be useful for ───────────────────────────────── -->
    <section class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-4">{tc.useCases.heading}</h2>
      <div class="space-y-4">
        {tc.useCases.items.map((item: { title: string; body: string }) => (
          <div class="border-l-2 border-gray-200 pl-4">
            <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-700 mb-1">{item.title}</p>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-500">{item.body}</p>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ── 7. Historical Coverage Status ──────────────────────────────────── -->
    <section class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-1">{tc.coverage.heading}</h2>
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 mb-5">{tc.coverage.subheading}</p>

      <!-- Current window alert -->
      <div class="border border-red-200 bg-red-50/60 rounded-md px-5 py-4 mb-8">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-red-700 mb-1">Current observation window: 2023–2026 only</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-red-600 leading-relaxed">{tc.coverage.currentSliceNote}</p>
      </div>

      <!-- ── Visual timeline ────────────────────────────────────────── -->
      <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-700 mb-2">{tc.coverage.timelineHeading}</h3>
      <!-- Legend -->
      <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center gap-4 mb-3 text-xs text-gray-500">
        <span class="flex items-center gap-1.5">
          <span class="inline-block w-3 h-3 rounded-sm bg-gray-300"></span>
          {tc.coverage.timelineLegend.missing}
        </span>
        <span class="flex items-center gap-1.5">
          <span class="inline-block w-3 h-3 rounded-sm bg-amber-300/80"></span>
          {tc.coverage.timelineLegend.partial}
        </span>
        <span class="flex items-center gap-1.5">
          <span class="inline-block w-3 h-3 rounded-sm bg-teal-400/80"></span>
          {tc.coverage.timelineLegend.full}
        </span>
      </div>

      {/* Timeline: 1995–2026 = 31 years. Segment widths as percentages. */}
      {/* 1995–2007 = 12 yr (38.7%), 2007–2023 = 16 yr (51.6%), 2023–2026 = 3 yr (9.7%) */}
      <div class="rounded-md overflow-hidden border border-gray-200 mb-2" style="height: 40px; display: flex;">
        {/* No data: 1995–2007 */}
        <div style="width:38.7%; background:#d1d5db;" class="flex items-center justify-center">
          <span class="text-xs text-gray-600 font-medium px-1" style="white-space:nowrap; overflow:hidden; text-overflow:ellipsis;">1995–2007</span>
        </div>
        {/* Partial: 2007–2023 */}
        <div style="width:51.6%; background:#fcd34d; opacity:0.75;" class="flex items-center justify-center border-l border-gray-200">
          <span class="text-xs text-amber-900 font-medium px-1" style="white-space:nowrap; overflow:hidden; text-overflow:ellipsis;">2007–2023</span>
        </div>
        {/* Full: 2023–2026 */}
        <div style="width:9.7%; background:#2dd4bf; opacity:0.75;" class="flex items-center justify-center border-l border-gray-200">
          <span class="text-xs text-teal-900 font-medium px-1" style="white-space:nowrap; overflow:hidden; text-overflow:ellipsis;">2023–26</span>
        </div>
      </div>
      {/* Event markers row */}
      <div class="relative mb-1" style="height: 22px;">
        {/* Dot-com peak ~2000: (2000-1995)/31 = 16.1% */}
        <div class="absolute text-xs text-gray-500" style="left:16.1%; transform:translateX(-50%);">
          <span class="block text-center">↑</span>
          <span style="white-space:nowrap; font-size:10px;">dot-com peak</span>
        </div>
        {/* GFC peak ~2007: (2007-1995)/31 = 38.7% */}
        <div class="absolute text-xs text-gray-500" style="left:38.7%; transform:translateX(-50%);">
          <span class="block text-center">↑</span>
          <span style="white-space:nowrap; font-size:10px;">GFC peak</span>
        </div>
        {/* Dataset start ~2023: 90.3% */}
        <div class="absolute text-xs text-teal-700 font-medium" style="left:90.3%; transform:translateX(-50%);">
          <span class="block text-center">↑</span>
          <span style="white-space:nowrap; font-size:10px;">dataset start</span>
        </div>
      </div>
      {/* Year labels */}
      <div class="relative mb-6" style="height: 16px;">
        {[
          { yr: '1995', pct: '0%' }, { yr: '2000', pct: '16.1%' }, { yr: '2007', pct: '38.7%' },
          { yr: '2015', pct: '64.5%' }, { yr: '2023', pct: '90.3%' }, { yr: '2026', pct: '100%' },
        ].map(({ yr, pct }) => (
          <span class="absolute text-xs text-gray-400" style={`left:${pct}; transform:translateX(-50%);`}>{yr}</span>
        ))}
      </div>

      <!-- ── Compact roadmap table ─────────────────────────────────────── -->
      <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-700 mb-3">{tc.coverage.phasesHeading}</h3>
      <div class="border border-gray-200 rounded-md overflow-hidden mb-6 text-xs">
        <table class="w-full border-collapse">
          <thead>
            <tr class="bg-gray-50 text-gray-500 uppercase tracking-wide">
              <th class="text-left px-3 py-2 font-medium">Phase</th>
              <th class="text-left px-3 py-2 font-medium">Period</th>
              <th class="text-left px-3 py-2 font-medium">Status</th>
              <th class="text-left px-3 py-2 font-medium">Available</th>
              <th class="text-left px-3 py-2 font-medium">Missing</th>
              <th class="text-left px-3 py-2 font-medium">Next step</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr class="border-t border-gray-100 bg-gray-50/30">
              <td class="px-3 py-2 font-medium text-gray-700">Dot-com</td>
              <td class="px-3 py-2 font-mono text-gray-600">1995–2003</td>
              <td class="px-3 py-2"><span class="bg-gray-200 text-gray-600 text-xs px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded">No data</span></td>
              <td class="px-3 py-2 text-gray-500">Nothing</td>
              <td class="px-3 py-2 text-gray-500">All fundamentals + prices</td>
              <td class="px-3 py-2 text-gray-500">New source required (Compustat / WRDS)</td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="border-t border-gray-100 bg-amber-50/20">
              <td class="px-3 py-2 font-medium text-gray-700">GFC</td>
              <td class="px-3 py-2 font-mono text-gray-600">2004–2011</td>
              <td class="px-3 py-2"><span class="bg-amber-100 text-amber-700 text-xs px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded border border-amber-200">Partial</span></td>
              <td class="px-3 py-2 text-amber-700">fundamentals.db: 30 US tickers, earnings + equity from 2007</td>
              <td class="px-3 py-2 text-gray-500">Historical closing prices</td>
              <td class="px-3 py-2 text-teal-700 font-medium">Fetch prices via yfinance → compute RG from fundamentals.db</td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="border-t border-gray-100 bg-amber-50/20">
              <td class="px-3 py-2 font-medium text-gray-700">Extended modern</td>
              <td class="px-3 py-2 font-mono text-gray-600">2012–2022</td>
              <td class="px-3 py-2"><span class="bg-amber-100 text-amber-700 text-xs px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded border border-amber-200">Partial</span></td>
              <td class="px-3 py-2 text-amber-700">fundamentals.db: full 30-ticker coverage</td>
              <td class="px-3 py-2 text-gray-500">Historical closing prices</td>
              <td class="px-3 py-2 text-teal-700 font-medium">Same as GFC — prices only</td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="border-t border-gray-100 bg-teal-50/20">
              <td class="px-3 py-2 font-medium text-gray-700">Current</td>
              <td class="px-3 py-2 font-mono text-gray-600">2023–2026</td>
              <td class="px-3 py-2"><span class="bg-teal-100 text-teal-700 text-xs px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded">Full</span></td>
              <td class="px-3 py-2 text-teal-700">77 companies, all indices, quarterly + annual</td>
              <td class="px-3 py-2 text-gray-400">—</td>
              <td class="px-3 py-2 text-gray-400">Active coverage</td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>
      <p class="text-xs text-gray-400 mb-7">{tc.coverage.fundamentalsDbNote}</p>

      <!-- Research hypotheses (condensed) -->
      <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-700 mb-3">{tc.coverage.whatWeWouldSee}</h3>
      <div class="space-y-2 mb-5">
        {tc.coverage.whatWeWouldSeeItems.map((item: { title: string; body: string }) => (
          <div class="flex gap-3 text-sm">
            <span class="text-gray-300 shrink-0 mt-0.5">–</span>
            <span><span class="font-medium text-gray-700">{item.title}: </span><span class="text-gray-500">{item.body}</span></span>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>
      <p class="text-xs text-gray-400 italic">{tc.coverage.disclaimer}</p>
    </section>

    <!-- ── 8. Limitations ────────────────────────────────────────────────── -->
    <section class="mb-8">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-4">{tc.limitations.heading}</h2>
      <div class="border border-gray-200 rounded-md p-5">
        <ul class="space-y-3">
          {tc.limitations.items.map((item: string) => (
            <li class="flex gap-3 text-sm text-gray-600">
              <span class="text-gray-300 shrink-0 mt-0.5">–</span>
              <span>{item}</span>
            </li>
          ))}
        </ul>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- General disclaimer -->
    <p class="text-xs text-gray-400 border-t border-gray-100 pt-6">{t.companyDetail.disclaimer}</p>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
